JOHANNESBURG - Marco Machona, the founding president of Zimbabwe’s newest political party, The African Democrats, said the army should have been firmer in dealing with President Robert Mugabe. Machona said the military has given Mugabe more room to manoeuvre. WATCH: Defiant Zim strongman Mugabe clings to power - eNCA He said it is not clear which way the courts will rule in the legal attempt to remove Mugabe after the latter failed to resign as expected on Sunday.  Zimbabwe's war veterans are turning to the courts in their bid to oust Mugabe as the country's president, while Zanu-PF set the impeachment ball rolling. eNCA